item.description:
Java 5 introduced the enhanced for loop (for-each),
which is shorter and easier to read than explicit
Iterator usage. This cleanup transforms:



Before:

Iterator<String> it = list.iterator();

while (it.hasNext()) {

    String s = it.next();

    // use s

}



After:

for (String s : list) {

    // use s

}



The cleanup only applies when the Iterator is not used
after the loop and it.remove() is not called.
